Class Common

  • java.lang.Object
    • Common

  • public abstract class Common
extends java.lang.Object

    This class just consists of static methods that make either some kind of operation, manipulate data to create objects, return of object lists and print of properties when a list of object is passed.

    The static final variables are mostly there to be used by the bin packing problem as a parameter when the method is called. These properties are declared as final since the size of CD and DVD are widely known and mostly remain as a constant figure.

    This class catches exception of the kind NullPointerException This is because it's one of the most common exceptions when using lists. IOException is also used to catch exception that are thrown from calling the readLine() method.

    References: Bin packing problem (First Fit)
    Author: Bastian Rieck
    Title: Basic Analysis of Bin-Packing Heuristics
    Page 2

    Author:
    Alexander Chetcuti

    • Method Detail

      • backupFirstFit

        public static java.util.List<java.util.List<Track>> backupFirstFit(java.util.List<Track> tracks,
                                                                   int diskSize)

        This method uses the first fit algorithm to calculate how many disks are needed to backup all the tracks in the music library. Although this algorithm does not provide the smallest amount of disks needed, it was chosen to preserve the order of the tracks when they are going to be backed up.

        Parameters:
        tracks - The list of tracks to be backed up.
        diskSize - The size of the disk that is going to be used for backup.
        Returns:
        The multi-dimensional list of track lists representing a list of disks needed each with a list of tracks to be written.

      • loadMusicians

        public static java.util.List<Musician> loadMusicians()

        Loads the JSON data saved in musicians.txt. The method reads the mentioned file and maps the loaded data using an external library. The library will initialise the class passed with the correct data in every property held in that class.

        Returns:
        The list of musicians that have been loaded from the JSON file.

      • loadBands

        public static java.util.List<Band> loadBands(java.util.List<Musician> musicians)

        Loads the JSON data saved in bands.txt. The method reads the mentioned file and maps the loaded data using an external library. The library will initialise the class passed with the correct data in every property held in that class.

        The method will also iterate a list of musicians to assign them to there bands if they require so.

        Parameters:
        musicians - The list of musicians to be checked to be added to a band.
        Returns:
        The list of bands that have been loaded from the JSON file.

      • loadTracks

        public static java.util.List<Track> loadTracks(java.util.List<Band> bands,
                                               java.util.List<Musician> musicians)

        Loads the JSON data saved in tracks.txt. The method reads the mentioned file and maps the loaded data using an external library. The library will initialise the class passed with the correct data in every property held in that class.

        The method will also iterate a list of bands and musicians to set the artist of each track in the list.

        Parameters:
        bands - The list of bands to be checked to be added to as an artist.
        musicians - The list of musicians to be checked to be added to as an artist.
        Returns:
        The list of bands that have been loaded from the JSON file.

      • loadAlbums

        public static java.util.List<Album> loadAlbums(java.util.List<Track> tracks,
                                               java.util.List<Band> bands,
                                               java.util.List<Musician> musicians)

        Loads the JSON data saved in albums.txt. The method reads the mentioned file and maps the loaded data using an external library. The library will initialise the class passed with the correct data in every property held in that class.

        The method will also iterate a list of bands and musicians to set the artist of each track in the list.

        The method will also iterate a list of tracks to be set as part of an album.

        Parameters:
        tracks - The list of tacks to be checked to be added as a track in the album.
        bands - The list of musicians to be checked to be added as an artist.
        musicians - The list of musicians to be checked to be added as an artist.
        Returns:
        The list of bands that have been loaded from the JSON file.

      • write

        public static void write(java.lang.Object object,
                         java.lang.String fileName)

        This Methods uses the same external library as the read method, to write and store information to a text file in a JSON format. The method ObjectMapper is used to handle the conversion of an object into JSON format.

        After the conversion is done the returned string is written to a file using the FileWriter class.

        Parameters:
        object - The object that needs to be written to a file.
        fileName - The name of the file excluding the extension of the file.
